        <para>
            <graphic fileref="images/fieldset.1.png" align="center" valign="middle" width="1000px"/>
        </para>
        <para>Below the tabs are the input fields. These are arranged in frames marked with thin lines. What is inside a frame belongs together.</para>
        <para>Each frame has a label, for example, "Names and Roles". On this label, there may be a question mark containing instructions about how to input information in the fields inside the frame.</para>
        <para>On the frame label there may also be a button with a '+' sign. This is for repeating a frame. In the frame shown above, there is only room for one name, but if a book has two authors, you can cause the frame to be repeated by clicking the '+' button, giving you two frames for Names and Roles and allowing you to input two authors.</para>
